      • SEMState

        public SEMState(java.lang.String itemname,
                int itemstate)
        Creates a default Semaphore controlled item. The default implementation allows any number of waiters to be registered and released for the given item--typically an Event.
        Parameters:
        itemname -
        itemstate -
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if itemname or itemstate are invalid.

      • addWaiter

        public com.ibm.staf.STAFResult addWaiter()
                                  throws java.lang.InterruptedException
        Blocks the calling thread--which should be from an EmbeddedHandle--until the item is triggered with another thread's call to releaseWaiters.

        Example call from an EmbeddedHandle:

          event.addWaiter();

        Returns:
        STAFResult.Ok when the item is available/posted/pulsed.
        Throws:
        java.lang.InterruptedException

      • addWaiter

        public com.ibm.staf.STAFResult addWaiter(long msTimeout)
                                  throws java.lang.InterruptedException
        Blocks the calling thread--which should be from an EmbeddedHandle-- until the item is triggered with another thread's call to releaseWaiters or the timeout has been reached.

        Example call from an EmbeddedHandle:

          STAFResult rc = event.addWaiter(100);

        Returns:
        STAFResult.Ok, or STAFResult.Timeout
        Throws:
        java.lang.InterruptedException - if the waiting thread gets interrupted.
